com.camsolute.code.camp.lib.dao

Interface UpdatesDaoInterface<T extends IsObjectInstance<T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - An object that must honor the IsObjectInstance contract. Example: OrderDao implements UpdatesDaoInterface<Order>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AddressDaoInterface, AddressRestInterface, AttributeDaoInterface, AttributeRestInterface, CustomerDaoInterface, CustomerRestInterface, DaoInterface<T>, InstanceDaoInterface<T>, ModelDaoInterface, ModelRestInterface, OrderDaoInterface, OrderPositionDaoInterface, OrderPositionRestInterface, OrderRestInterface, ProductDaoInterface, ProductRestInterface, TouchPointDaoInterface, TouchPointRestInterface
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AddressDao, AddressRest, AttributeDao, AttributeRest, CustomerDao, CustomerRest, DescriptionDao, ModelDao, ModelRest, OrderDao, OrderPositionDao, OrderPositionRest, OrderRest, ProductDao, ProductRest, TouchPointDao, TouchPointRest

    public interface UpdatesDaoInterface<T extends IsObjectInstance<T>>
    Objects that honor this contract provide access to CAMP system updates tables. Within the CAMP framework updates tables provide a channel for objects that honor the IsObjectInstance contract to communicate changes to interested observers. The CAMP framework does not provide a service for observers to register and automatically be informed when objects of interest publish changes there. Observers are identified by a target identifier string. This identifier must be used when an object registers in an updates table. Observers therefore must do poll for updates table at their own discretion. Observers must also deregister an object from an updates table. This will require some form of coordination if multiple observers of an object exist (such coordination could be achieved by implementing a subscription service which would handle polling and publishing changes to observers that have subscribed to the service).
    Author:
    Christopher Campbell
